  "name": "Bleached Horizon",
  "mood": "Submerged",
  "engines": ["Obrix"],
  "description": "Maximum bleach rate with zero stress recovery. Play sustained high-register passages and the reef gradually loses its harmonics — a slow spectral death that mirrors real coral bleaching. Hit STATE RESET to restore life.",
  "tags": ["obrix", "biophonic", "stateful", "bleach", "signature"],
  "tier": "signature",
  "guru_bin": {
    "retreat": "OBRIX — Wave 4 Signature Campaign",
    "retreat_date": "2026-04-06",
    "scripture": ["Verse 14: Stateful Synthesis — Bleaching", "Gospel 5: The Sound of Ecological Loss"],
    "revelation": "bleachRate=0.7 with stressDecay=0 creates a one-way spectral degradation that can only be reversed by the STATE RESET parameter. A sonic metaphor for irreversible environmental damage.",
    "god": null,
    "flock_note": "This preset is an artistic statement. It sounds beautiful at first, then gradually loses richness. The player must decide when to reset.",
    "diagnosis": "Bleached Horizon uses stateful synthesis as narrative — the timbre tells a story of loss over time. It demonstrates that OBRIX's state system is not just a DSP trick but a compositional tool."
  },
